### Login API Tests for VS Code REST Client Extension
### Install the "REST Client" extension by Humao to use this file

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:8080/api/health

###

### 2. Successful Login - Admin User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

###

### 3. Successful Login - Regular User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user",
  "password": "password"
}

###

### 4. Successful Login - Demo User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "demo",
  "password": "demo"
}

###

### 5. Failed Login - Invalid Credentials
POST http://localhost:8080/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "invalid",
  "password": "wrong"
}

###

### 6. Failed Login - Missing Password
POST http://localhost:8080/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin"
}

###

### 7. Get User Profile (Replace TOKEN with actual token from login response)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/profile
Authorization: Bearer mock-jwt-token-REPLACE-WITH-ACTUAL-TOKEN-admin

###

### 8. Get User Profile - Invalid Token
GET http://localhost:8080/api/profile
Authorization: Bearer invalid-token

###

### 9. Get User Profile - Missing Authorization Header
GET http://localhost:8080/api/profile

###

### 10. Logout
POST http://localhost:8080/api/logout
Authorization: Bearer mock-jwt-token-REPLACE-WITH-ACTUAL-TOKEN-admin

###

### Instructions:
### 1. Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code
### 2. Open this file in VS Code
### 3. Click "Send Request" above each request
### 4. For profile tests, first run a login request and copy the token from the response
### 5. Replace "REPLACE-WITH-ACTUAL-TOKEN" with the actual token value